<subSubSection id="F4C86558BD51FF9F9EDFF918DC57DDAB" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD51FF9F9EDFF918DC57DDAB" blockId="4.[151,1436,1693,1936]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD51FF9F9EDFF918DE4FDC93" bold="true" box="[151,274,1693,1719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head strongly lenticular; mandible with lamella, teeth equal or subequal; eye strongly emarginated opposite antennal socket; temple short; notauli absent; central 0.3 or more of mesopleural furrow not impressed, indicated by weakly raised mesepimeron; scutellum slightly concave to convex; propodeum rugose to reticulate, spiracle elongate; apex of propodeum close to apex of hind coxa; areolet absent; fore wing 2m-cu vein vertical; nervellus intercepted below middle; tarsal claws pectinate; metasoma long and strongly compressed; postpetiole swollen and bulbous; male parameres rod-like or not; ovipositor short, straight or upcurved, not projecting beyond apex of metasoma and with a distinct notch subapically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
